essing their performance against the budget they are given. In some organizations, this evaluation can affect bonuses and promotions.\"", "\"COMMUNICATION THROUGH BUDGETS\":\"Communication through budgets involves superiors using budgets to communicate their expectations to the managers below them.\"", "\"ETHICAL AND SUSTAINABILITY CONSIDERATIONS IN BUDGETING\":\"Ethical and sustainability considerations in budgeting involve incorporating ethical and sustainability elements into the budget-setting process to manage risks and opportunities related to sustainability.\"", "\"SUSTAINABLE BUDGETING\":\"Sustainable budgeting focuses on how budgeting decisions affect sustainability and societal well-being measures, such as climate impact and local community effects.\"", "\"LONG-TERM PLANNING\":\"Long-term planning involves setting out the long-term, strategic objectives of the organization and determining the actions needed to achieve those objectives.\"", "\"MISSION STATEMENT\":\"A mission statement describes the reason for an organization's existence, including its business type, policies, standards of behavior, values, and culture.\"", "\"STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES\":\"STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES\" are high-level goals that support an organization's mission and guide its performance measurement and management. These objectives are specific and quantifiable goals that an organization must achieve to fulfill its mission.", "\"UNIT OBJECTIVES\":\"Unit objectives are goals set for each business unit within an organization, consistent with the strategic objectives.\"", "\"PERFORMANCE HIERARCHY\":The performance hierarchy is a structure used to set out the long-term, strategic objectives of an organization. It organizes these objectives into a structured framework, typically including the mission, corporate objectives, subsidiary objectives, and business unit objectives. This hierarchical arrangement ensures that the organization's mission and strategic objectives are clearly defined and systematically cascaded down to the various business units, aligning all levels of the organization towards common goals.", "\"ROLE OF BUDGETING IN LONG-TERM PLANNING\":The role of budgeting in long-term planning involves creating detailed financial plans for the budget period that align with the long-term strategic plan. This process includes implementing the long-term plan for the budget period, with the budget being more detailed than the long-term plan.", "\"SETTING STRATEGIES\":\"Setting strategies involves determining the actions needed to achieve the organization's objectives, often outlined in a long-term plan.\"", "\"MASTER BUDGET\":\"The master budget consolidates all subsidiary budgets and is presented as a statement of profit or loss, a statement of financial position, and a cash flow statement. It requires board approval and ensures control over operations and expenditures.\"", "\"FUNCTIONAL BUDGETS\":\"Functional budgets are prepared by operational managers and include primary budgets such as sales, production, materials, labor, and capital. These budgets must be prepared in sequence and reviewed for consistency.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}